cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.HC 

This paper deals with the interpretation of deep neural networks for medical image classification, specifically mammogram classification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a framework for discovering interpretable representations, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG - Learning). The use of expert annotation and correlation with ground truth radiology reports suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI - Artificial Intelligence). The paper deals with medical imaging, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM - Multimedia). Finally, the paper proposes a method for generating explanations, which is relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC - Human-Computer Interaction).
